'''Buysdorp''' ke village nyane go feta [[Mmasepala Setereke tša Vhembe]] wa diporofense [[Limpopo]] kamoka [[Afrika Borwa]].

A rural coloured community located 14 km from [[Vivo, Limpopo|Vivo]], on the R522 road to [[Louis Trichardt, Limpopo|Louis Trichardt]], Buysdorp was named after Coenraad de Buys, the “King of the Bastards” in Sarah Millin's fictional account of his life.<ref name=uww>{{cite web|last=Ebersohn|first=Kathleen|title=Ways of Loving: Being Coloured, Being a Man in Buysdorp|url=http://wiredspace.wits.ac.za/bitstream/handle/10539/11727/0500925D_KEbersohn_20120330.pdf?sequence=1|publisher=University of the Witwatersrand|accessdate=8 January 2014|author=|year=2012}}</ref>

